@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{tachi}}" grammar="@KJ{{accomplished}}"}}

<body>

<h1>@KJ{{accomplished}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <em>personal pronoun</em> + @KJ{{accomplished}}
<li> <em>human proper noun</em> + @KJ{{accomplished}}
<li> <em>human noun</em> + @KJ{{accomplished}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{accomplished}} is a suffix attached to personal pronouns or human nouns. It acts as a plural marker.
</p>

<p>
It may be attached to:
<ol>
<li> a personal pronoun: @KJ{{private^accomplished}} (we)
<li> a human proper noun: @KJ{{mountain^rice*field}}@HI{{san}}@KJ{{accomplished}} (Mr. Yamada and others)
<li> a human noun: @KJ{{child^submit^accomplished}} (children)
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{he^woman^accomplished}} is permitted but @KJ{{he}} cannot take @KJ{{accomplished}}.
</p>

<h2> References </h2>

<ol>
